/**
 * hir: AST → HIR conversion and HirProgram assembly.
 *
 * This file has been split into sub-modules:
 *
 *   hir/convert/core.nx   — convert_expr (the primary public entry point),
 *                           convert_expr_toplevel, convert_stmts,
 *                           convert_params, match-case / catch-arm / handler-arm
 *                           conversion, and all helpers. convert_expr and
 *                           convert_stmts are mutually recursive (SCC), so they
 *                           cannot be split further without circular imports.
 *
 *   hir/build/defs.nx     — process_defs / process_top_level / process_tl_let,
 *                           synthesize_handler, make_hir_external,
 *                           convert_cap_sigs, WIT-mapping helpers,
 *                           infer_{tparams,params,ret}_from_expr,
 *                           infer_constant_type.
 *
 *   hir/build/accum.nx    — empty_accum, register_exn_variant,
 *                           expand_groups_in_{functions,handler_bindings,...},
 *                           accum_to_program.
 *
 * Pattern-shape conversion (convert_pattern, pattern_binders) remains in
 * src/ir/hir/pattern.nx.
 *
 * Import from the appropriate sub-module directly. This file is intentionally
 * left as a documentation pointer only (Nexus has no re-export syntax).
 *
 * Does not own:
 * - HIR type definitions (see src/ir/hir/types.nx)
 * - Reachability analysis / dead-code filtering (see src/ir/hir/reachability.nx)
 * - Iterative lazy-body resolution loop (see src/ir/hir/demand.nx)
 * - Handler-function name mangling (see src/common/naming.nx)
 * - Rdr-name resolution (see src/ir/rdrname.nx, src/ir/symtab.nx)
 */
